--> TesTNG annotations is a piece of code which is inserted inside a program or business logic used to control the flow of executionof test methods
--> List of Annotations
       --> BeforeSuite:- Method will run before the execution of all the methods in the suite.
       --> AfterSuite:- Method will run after the execution of all the methods in the suite.
       --> BeforeTest:- Method will be executed before the execution of all the test methods of available classes belonging to that folder.
       --> AfterTest:- Method will be executed after the execution of all the test methods of available classes belonging to that folder.
       --> BeforeClass:- Method will be executed before the first method of the current class is invoked.
       --> AfterClass:- Method will be invoked after the execution of all the test methods of the current class.
       --> BeforeMethod:- Method will be executed before each test method will run.
       --> AfterMethod:- Method will be executed after the execution of each test method.
       --> BeforeGroup:- Method run only once for a group before the execution of all the cases belonging to that group.
       --> AfterGroup:- Method run only once for a group after the execution of all the cases belonging to that group.

--> Hierarchy of the TestNG Annotations:
      -->BeforeSuite-->BeforeTest--> BeforeClass--> BeforeMethod
                      Test
      --> AfterMethod--> AfterClass-->AfterTest--> AfterSuite